  "doc_id": "38844",
  "text": "The in vitro methylation of H3K4 by the KMT2A/MLL1 SET domain is strongly enhanced by phosphorylation of the histone peptide substrate at serine 10 [33] , raising the possibility that phosphorylation of this residue may influence the gene regulatory activity of the KMT2A/MLL1 complex in vivo. Phosphorylation of H3S10 in chromatin can occur through the action of the closely related kinases Msk1 and Msk2 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , so we explored the possibility that Msk1 might operate as part of the KMT2A/MLL1 complex. Msk1 is constantly expressed in the cells but is active only after (auto-) phosphorylation and allosteric changes induced by ERK1 or 2 [CITATION_3] . The antibody used for these experiments is specific for Msk1 phosphorylated at S360, one of the last residues to become phosphorylated, and detects active Msk1 [CITATION_4] . In three different cell types-human lymphoblastoid cells (LCLs), mouse embryo fibroblasts (MEFs) and human embryonic kidney cells (HEKs)-material precipitated with antibodies to KMT2A contained readily detectable amounts of Msk1 (Fig. 1a) . The protein often migrated as a double band, possibly due to allosteric changes and/or differences in phosphorylation status (Fig. 1a) . Conversely, antibodies to Msk1 immunoprecipitated KMT2A/MLL1 (Fig. 1b , full-length blots from 1A and 1B are shown in Additional file 1). To validate this interaction, FLAG-tagged KMT2A/MLL1 was overexpressed in HEK293 cells and the associated complex purified (Fig. 1c) . Western blot analysis of the immunoprecipitated complex confirmed that it contained the FLAG-tagged KMT2A/MLL1 and also Msk1, but not NFκB, a known interaction partner of Msk1 [CITATION_5] readily detected in the lysate (Fig. 1c) . It seems that the KMT2A/MLL1-Msk1 interaction is specific, stable and present in a range of mouse and human cell types.",
